args:
Lily wants to celebrate Dragonyule, but with
the empire on the offensive, that doesn't look
possible...until an unlikely solution is found.
Dressed in Saint Starfall outfits, Lily and Victor
set off for battle to save the holiday season!
We'll chop you down to size!
It all started several weeks earlier...
What do you mean we can't celebrate\nDragonyule this year?!

It's a shame, but we've received word that
fiends and the imperial army are stirring
up even more trouble than usual right now.
This is no time for merriment.
But I was going to dress up as\nSaint Starfall and everything...
I know, Lily. I'm sorry. But if we don't\nsecure the safety of the people first,\nthere won't be anything TO celebrate.
I think the best present we can give\neveryone this year is the gift of peace.
Welcome back! How did everything look?
It's as we feared. The imperial army is\nnoticeably more active at present.
I did what I could to obstruct them, but\nthere was only so much I could do alone.
I feared as much. We're all a little short\non numbers right now, but I'll see if I can\nsend some more people your way.
No, that would be too risky. We don't\nwant to give the empire an advantage\nover us on any front.
But the burden on you would be too heavy\nwere we to leave things as they are!
I'll be fine. I'm used to fighting solo.\nFor the present, I'll focus on obstructing\nthem and slowly reducing their numbers.
You need only send reinforcements once\nthey're available.
Actually, I think she could be of help,\nVictor.
Preposterous! I cannot take a CHILD with\nme to fight a war!
Please. Let me come. I wanna help\nprotect Dragonyule for everyone!
I think you'll be surprised what\nshe's capable of. She'll pull her\nweight, trust me.
(I can't believe what I'm hearing...\nBut {player_name} doesn't seem\nto be joking.)
She'll keep you in check too, I wager.
(Ah. He's proposing this knowing I'm\nless likely to take...drastic measures so\nlong as she's watching me.)
So she's to keep an eye on me, then.\nI suppose I can't refuse.
I will do what I must to make sure the\nempire's deeds don't go unpunished.
Oh, but I have one more favor to ask!
I'm going to need an explanation.\n...Stat.
It's a Saint Starfall outfit.\nI think it rather suits you.
How well it suits me is hardly the issue.\nWhy am I being asked to wear it?
Did Lily not ask you to go and deliver\ngifts with her?
That is Saint Starfall's role.\nThus, you must dress for the part.
C'mon, Victor. We've got this in the bag—\nthe PRESENT bag, that is! Hee hee.
We're gonna beat up the baddies AND\nspread holiday cheer everywhere we go!
You see? And besides, your face is\nwell known to the empire, is it not?
Surely they're less likely to ascertain\nyour identity if you are dressed like that.
No one would expect the former leader\nof a group of mercenaries to be dressed\nin such a jolly manner.
Okey doke, Victor!\nLet's be awesome Saint Starfalls together!
Very well. Whatever it takes to stop the\nempire having their way.
That's the spirit. Do be careful, you two.
You bet! Let me just hoist up all\nthese presents. Heeeeave...
*pant* Um, they're too heavy for me...
Give them here. I'll handle it.
Whoa! You made that look EASY!\nYou're so cool, Victor.
Okay, NOW we can go!\nSee ya later, everyone!
I've never seen a more unlikely duo...\nI do hope they will be all right.
You're going to end up with a face full of\ndirt if you don't watch where you're going.
I'll be careful! But this so much fuuun!\nHow far are we going? Are we there yet?\n...Oh! What just moved over there?
(She looks like an ordinary child to me—\none with neither the strength nor the\nknow-how to fight.)
(Is she really going to help in defeating\nthe empire?)
We're gonna make this a Dragonyule to\nremember! Awww yeah!
(I have a bad feeling about this...)
